    {
      "id": "b898f4d4f274a61e96d28242e8f9b63cc59ed416",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-08-04 23:05:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nThe patch looks good to me, though there is a suggestion there.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7abce64425a02bb436ce95af3db11bc1a5fcf9af",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-08-05 01:26:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nPlease look back through git/cvs history for the reason that this change was made in the first place. I believe it was because there were some 1.8.x clients that would not set o_gr (o_seq) = 0 in all code paths. Fixing this problem in 1.8.7 would be helpful, but not a complete solution, since not all customers using 2.1 will also be using 1.8.7 (when it is released).\n\nIf no 1.8.x clients set OBD_MD_FLGROUP but forget to set o_gr, then this change is safe. Otherwise this patch may not be correct.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "da3cdc21d022ad6a2740e1d663470ef02f6259eb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-08-05 02:54:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI've checked the git log, and seems this piece of code is introduced by wangdi, but I didn't see the reason in the commit comment. Wangdi, do you still remember why it's introduced?\n\nAnd I also checked the 1.8 server code, looks it only fix the o_gr to 0 when the OBD_MD_FLGROUP is not set, which means if 1.8 client has the bug of sending random o_gr with OBD_MD_FLGROUP flag, then 1.8 server will run into trouble either.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "6a5ec79467dd046a4da4765e5887ed5b753d21c1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-08-05 03:28:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: No score\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\n",
